Sentencas: Nanocomposite electrodes of (Sr0.7Pr0.3)(0.95)TiO3 +/-delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 are directly prepared by spray-pyrolysis deposition on Zr0.82Y0.16O1.92 electrolytes and their properties are compared with those obtained by the traditional screen-printing powder method.
Titulo: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells based on titanate nanocomposite electrodes

Sentencas: The structural, microstructural and electrical characteristics are investigated for their potential use as both cathode and anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells.
Titulo: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells based on titanate nanocomposite electrodes

Sentencas: The nanocomposite electrodes with reduced particle size similar to 30 nm achieved a polarization resistance at 700 degrees C of 0.50 and 0.46 Omega cm(2) in air and pure H-2, respectively, outperforming those obtained for the analogous screen-printed electrodes with particle size of 450 nm, i.e. 4.8 and 3.9 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells based on titanate nanocomposite electrodes

Sentencas: An electrolyte-supported cell with symmetrical electrodes reached a maximum and stable power density of 354 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. These results demonstrate that the performance of electrode materials with modest electrochemical properties but high phase stability, such as doped-SrTiO3, can be highly improved by preparing nanocomposite electrodes directly on the electrolyte surface.
Titulo: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells based on titanate nanocomposite electrodes
